□ Contribution

Lasan JS is an open-source project, and we welcome your contributions! Here
are some ways you can get involved:
  1. Report a Bug: Found a bug? Let us know by opening an issue.
  2. Contribute Code: Have a solution or improvement? Submit a pull request.
  3. Improve Documentation: Help us make our documentation better.
  4. Suggest a Feature: Have an idea for a new feature? We’d love to hear it.

If you have any suggestions or want to contribute, feel free to open an issue
or a pull request. Your contributions are invaluable to us!

Love Lasan? Give our repo a star ⭒ to support us!

PS:
  ⬦ This may not be the best, but if something can do it, it does it very well.
  ⬦ Lasan stands for a Lightweight, Adaptable, Scalable, Agile, and Nimble web framework.
